This paper deals with the robustness of deep neural networks on videos, which involves both spatial and temporal features. Therefore, the most likely category is computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of Lipschitz continuity, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also addresses the problem of adversarial attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper evaluates its framework on a video dataset, which is related to multimedia (cs.MM).
